    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf I'm partway through a quickfix list, and then I do something to refresh the quickfix list, I lose my location in the list.\n\nHere's an example of that happening:\n\n![demo](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a4e01b91-dfea-4167-b9a5-4b6c32b1695b)\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI'd prefer for my quickfix list to preserve my current location, or whatever entry in the list is nearest wherever I was.\n\nI was able to hack this together by monkeypatching `vim.fn.setqflist` in Lua. Here's that hack in plugin form: https://github.com/jfly/sticky-quickfix.nvim.\n\nThis isn't perfect: it wouldn't play nicely with Vimscript code that calls `:call setqflist(...)`. There are probably other issues with it that I'm not aware of.",
