            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@glepnir, this isn't a diagnostics issue. I just used LSP diagnostics to try to provide a simple example.\n\n@justinmk here's a simple vim file to demonstrate the issue. I agree that this behavior only makes sense if `'r'` is passed, which I didn't show in my original example.\n\n```vimscript\n\" Dead simple script to convert every line in the current buffer into\n\" an entry in the quickfix list.\n\"\n\" This replaces the current quickfix list.\n\" Run with `:source %`\n\nlet qflist = []\n\nlet line_count = line('$')\nfor lnum in range(1, line_count)\n    let line_text = getline(lnum)\n    let bufnr = bufnr('%')\n    call add(qflist, {'bufnr': bufnr, 'lnum': lnum, 'text': line_text})\nendfor\n\ncall setqflist(qflist, 'r')\n\n\" Open the quickix list.\ncopen\n```\n\nAnd here it is in action:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9d2b48a3-8824-4813-9ab5-cd13bd8f0b63\n\n\n> But should be requested/implemented at https://github.com/vim/vim\n\nSounds good! I've filed https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/15839. I'm ok closing this issue in favor of that one.\n",
            "created_at": "2024-10-09T16:23:03Z",
